# EstateNet Frontend Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and update with your values

# =============================================================================
# API Configuration
# =============================================================================

# Backend API URL
# - For local web development: Use localhost (default, no need to set)
# - For phone testing on LAN: Set to your PC's local IP address
# - Format: http://YOUR_IP:PORT/api
# - Example: EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3002/api

# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3002/api

# =============================================================================
# How to find your PC's IP address:
# =============================================================================
# 
# Windows:
#   1. Open Command Prompt
#   2. Run: ipconfig
#   3. Look for "IPv4 Address" under your active network adapter
#   4. Example: 192.168.1.100
#
# macOS/Linux:
#   1. Open Terminal
#   2. Run: ifconfig | grep "inet "
#   3. Look for your local network IP (usually starts with 192.168 or 10.0)
#
# =============================================================================
# Common Scenarios:
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. Local Web Development (default):
#    - No .env needed
#    - Uses: http://localhost:3002/api
#
# 2. Testing on Phone (same WiFi network):
#    - Create .env file
#    - Set: EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://YOUR_PC_IP:3002/api
#    - Example: EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3002/api
#    - Restart Expo: npm start
#
# 3. Testing on Phone (different network):
#    - Not recommended for development
#    - Consider using ngrok or similar tunneling service
#
# =============================================================================
# Important Notes:
# =============================================================================
#
# - After changing .env, restart the development server
# - Make sure backend is running on the specified port
# - Ensure firewall allows connections on the backend port
# - The backend must be bound to 0.0.0.0 (not just localhost)
#
